<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf3c6582c-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc" identifier="/us/usc/t35/s152"><num value="152">§ 152.</num><heading> Issue of patent to assignee</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Patents may be granted to the assignee of the inventor of record in the Patent and Trademark Office, upon the application made and the specification sworn to by the inventor, except as otherwise provided in this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf3c6582d-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">(<ref href="/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950">July 19, 1952, ch. 950</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/66/804">66 Stat. 804</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/93/596/s1">Pub. L. 93–596, § 1</ref>, <date date="1975-01-02">Jan. 2, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/1949">88 Stat. 1949</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf3c6582e-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf3c6582f-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 44 (R.S. 4895).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Language is changed and the reference to reissue is omitted in view of the general provision in section 251.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf3c65830-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf3c65831-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1975—<ref href="/us/pl/93/596">Pub. L. 93–596</ref> substituted “Patent and Trademark Office” for “Patent Office”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idf3c65832-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idf3c65833-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1975 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/93/596">Pub. L. 93–596</ref> effective <date date="1975-01-02">Jan. 2, 1975</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/93/596/s4">section 4 of Pub. L. 93–596</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s1111">section 1111 of Title 15</ref>, Commerce and Trade.</p>
</note>
</notes>
